JOHANNESBURG - Kwaito singer and producer Arthur Mafokane is facing common assault charges after a reported fight this week with his girlfriend. A police spokesperson said that, after spending Thursday night in jail, Mofokane appeared in the Midrand Magistrate s Court the next day.According to Sunday World reports, Mafokate had dragged his girlfriend, singer Cici, into the street with his car.Cici, whose real name is Busisiwe Twala, filed charges against the singer-turned-music-label-founder.eNCA could not independently confirm the allegations. police declined to comment on an ongoing case.The National Prosecuting Authority referred the matter to the Midrand police for further investigation. eNCA